did.abstract: David A. Clarke (1943-1997) served as the Ward One Representative on the Council of the District of Columbia from 1975 to 1982, and served as Chairman of the Council between 1983 and 1991. In 1993, he was elected to complete the term of the late John A. Wilson, and in 1995 he was reinstated to serve another four-year term, where he served until his death in 1997. This collection contains correspondence, subject files, campaign and election records, clippings, legal documents, photographs, and artifacts. Materials date from 1974 to 1997.
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged in two series according to when the papers were received. Part 1 of the collection was received in 1990, and Part 2 was received after Clarke's death in 1997.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: David A. Clarke (1943-1997) served as the Ward One Representative on the Council of the District of Columbia from 1975 to 1982, and served as Chairman of the Council between 1983 and 1991. In 1993, he was elected to complete the term of the late John A. Wilson, and in 1995 he was reinstated to serve another four-year term, where he served until his death in 1997.

Clarke was a member of the National Board of Directors of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference and the NAACP Legal Defense Fund-Washington Committee. He grew up in the Skyland and Shaw areas of Washington, D.C. and attended public schools in the District. He received a B.A. in religion from George Washington University and a J.D. from Howard University School of Law.
The David A. Clarke School of Law at the University of the District of Columbia was named for Clarke in 1998.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use note
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition note
acqinfo.p: Gift of the Honorable David A. Clarke, Chairman of the Council of the District of Columbia, 1990 [1991.002]. Additional accessions were received from the estate of David A. Clarke in 1997 and 2000.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, subject files, campaign and election records, clippings, legal documents, photographs, audio and video recordings, and artifacts. Materials in subject files pertain to D.C. legislation, organizations, neighborhoods, businesses, and individuals. Correspondence includes letters from constituents as well as legislative drafts and proposals, reports of the Council, memoranda, articles, and invitations to events. Materials date from 1974 to 1997.

These papers were received in two separate donations, one in 1990 and the second after Clarke's death in 1997. These accessions became two separate series. Before ordering a box, please note the series to which it belongs.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation note
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains reports, correspondence, clippings, proposals, and legislation, all arranged by subject or proper name. The material dates from 1976-1990, and was donated in 1990.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains three subseries: Correspondence, Subject files, and Campaigns and elections. The material was donated in 1997 and 2000.

Although they were separated into subseries in the finding aid, the folders in this series were not physically rearranged and all original folder titles were maintained. Therefore, this collection may take longer to use for research as more boxes will have to be explored to ensure finding all relevant documents.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: A portion of this subseries is arranged chronologically, a portion is arranged alphabetically, and a portion is arranged according to subject.

Although they were separated into subseries in the finding aid, the folders were not physically rearranged and all original folder titles were maintained. Therefore, this collection may take longer to use for research as more boxes will have to be explored to ensure finding all relevant documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains reports, correspondence, clippings, proposals, legislation, awards and certificates, budget information, press releases, legal documents, and reading files. The material dates from 1977-1997. Particular topics of interest include the D.C. Coalition of Conscience, gun control, the death penalty, economic development, land use, the Pilot District Project, the Poor People's Campaign, the Sentencing Guidelines Commission, and the Southern Christian Leadership Conference.
